******
[3] Shandong
Date: 12 May 2017
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news_detail?action=ql&uid=MjI0OA&pd=YXRsbXBw&newsId=19392


According to the authorites, Liaocheng city reported one human H7N9 AIV fatal case on 12 May 2017.

The 41-year-old male patient was a resident of Guotun town of Yanggu county of Liaocheng city. He worked in a local live poultry processing enterprise, job description as hanging the live chickens onto the hook of the automatic processing line. He had history of hypertension, chronic cough, and obesity. The patient had symptoms such as fatigue, fever, headache on the afternoon of 7 May 2017 and went to a local clinic in Guotun town for treatment.

With no improvement on initial treatment, he was admitted to Liaocheng city people's hospital respiratory unit and was diagnosed as an unknown pneumonia case on 11 May 2017. On the night of 11 May 2017, his sample was tested positive for H7N9 by the influenza reference lab, and the results were confirmed by the provincial CDC on the morning of 12 May 2017; he died on 12 May 2017. Close contacts of the patient are under medical monitoring.

Epidemiological investigation revealed the patient's job routine required live poultry contact (he had worked in this job for 1.5 years) and he bought 2 chickens (whether live or processed remains unknown) on 29 Apr 2017, 8 days prior to the onset of his symptoms.

--
